    <p class="section-number">07 · Why customers call us back</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What separates our pilot/thermocouple service.</h2>
    <ul class="reasons-list">
      <li><strong>Millivolt meter on every gas call.</strong> We measure rather than guess. Every "needs new gas valve" diagnosis from competitors should get a millivolt test first; about 60% turn into a $200 thermocouple fix instead.</li>
      <li><strong>Parts on the van.</strong> Heat &amp; Glo, Heatilator, Majestic, Valor, Mendota common thermocouples and thermopiles. Most "won't stay lit" calls are one-visit fixes.</li>
      <li><strong>Coastal salt-air expertise.</strong> Marine-grade thermocouples and corrosion-resistant terminal hardware on coastal-route vans for Newport, Manhattan Beach, Marina del Rey, Malibu, Pacific Palisades.</li>
      <li><strong>Age-matched component replacement.</strong> When the thermocouple fails at year 6, the thermopile is usually within 1-2 years of the same failure window. We offer to replace the pair to prevent a callback, but it's the customer's call.</li>
